CAS Server Installation Guide

1. Get Latest cas release zip from site : http://www.jasig.org/cas/download
   Example : cas-server-3.4.11-release.zip

2. Unzip file cas release zip:

3. Create a new web project in Netbeans:
   Example: cas-server

4. Unzip cas-server-webapp-3.4.11.war to get library  that in cas-server-3.4.11\modules\cas-server-webapp-3.4.11.war\WEB-INF\lib\*
   Then set cas-server library.

5. Copy cas-server-3.4.11\cas-server-webapp\src\main\webapp to 
   cas-server\lib
   
6. Copy cas-server-3.4.11\cas-server-webapp\src\main\java to
   cas-server\src\java
   Copy D:\workspace\cas\cas-server-3.4.11\cas-server-webapp\src\main\resources\META-INF\persistence.xml to cas-server\src\conf\persistence.xml

7. Change persistence.xml

    <provider>org.hibernate.ejb.HibernatePersistence</provider>
    <jta-data-source>jdbc/cas</jta-data-source>
    <properties>
      <property name="hibernate.hbm2ddl.auto" value="update"/>
    </properties>
	
8. configure jdbc/cas in glassfish server

9. Deploy

10. Testing for checking deployment successfully:
    The default SimpleTestUsernamePasswordAuthenticationHandler authenticates UsernamePasswordCredentials where the username equals the password.